# MrSurety QA – Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SETUP (one-time):
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # Edit .env if you need different credentials, then just run:
#   npm install && npx playwright install chromium
#   npx playwright test
#
# Values in .env override any MRSURETY_BASE_URL or credential variables that
# were previously exported in your shell.  This means if you ever ran:
#   export MRSURETY_BASE_URL=https://staging.mrsurety.com
# you can fix it by simply running: cp .env.example .env
#
# NEVER commit .env – it is already listed in .gitignore.
#
# Source: Christopher's "MR SURETY – TESTING GUIDE FOR QA TEAM"
#   Part 1 – User Types, Part 8 – Test User Credentials Template

# ─── App URL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is the live production URL provided by Christopher.
# Only change this if you are testing against a different environment
# (e.g. a local dev server or a staging deployment).
MRSURETY_BASE_URL=https://frontend-tan-five-46.vercel.app

# ─── Admin (credentials provided by Christopher – do not change) ─────────────
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@mrsurety.com
ADMIN_PASSWORD=MrSurety2026!

# ─── Doc #5 specific test accounts ──────────────────────────────────────────
DOC5_TESTOWNER_EMAIL=testowner@mrsurety.com
DOC5_TESTOWNER_PASSWORD=MrSurety2026!
